headline: Uber Eats Expands Partnerships with Beloved Local Grocers
summary: SAN FRANCISCO, July 01, 2025--Uber Eats (NYSE:UBER) is making it even easier for customers to access fresh groceries from their favorite local and regional stores. Uber Eats has recently expanded its grocery delivery service to include new partnerships with the much-loved local brands Big Y and King Kullen in the Northeast, Superlo Foods, Lunds & Byerlys, and Foxtrot in the Midwest and Texas, and Vallarta Supermarkets in California.

headline: Wedbush says 40% of Uber mobility gross bookings exposed to potential AV risk
summary: Wedbush says that while the firm thinks the near-term financial impact to established ride-sharing platforms is limited, over time, Wedbush expects autonomous vehicles will disrupt the current status quo. The firm notes that 40% of Uber‘s (UBER) mobility gross bookings are most exposed to potential AV risk, with similar proportion of Lyft‘s (LYFT) core business.
